  "Question": "<p>For any two positive integers <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_568\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"{n_{1},n_{2}}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>, the relationship between their greatest common divisor and their least common multiple is given by</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_569\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\text{lcm}(n_{1},n_{2})=\\frac{n_{1}n_{2}}{\\gcd(n_{1},n_{2})}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\text</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>l</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>c</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>gcd</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>If I have a set of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_570\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"r\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>r</mi> </math></span> positive integers <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_571\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"{n_{1},n_{2},n_{3},...,n_{r}}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>, does the same relationship hold? Is it true that</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_572\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\text{lcm}(n_{1},n_{2},n_{3},...,n_{r})=\\frac{\\prod_{i=1}^{r}n_{i}}{gcd(n_{1},%\nn2,n_{3},...,n_{r})}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\text</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>l</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>c</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msub> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u220f</mo> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mi>r</mi> </msubsup> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>c</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msub> <mo>,</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>,</mo> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msub> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>I feel like this should be easy to prove, but I'm struggling to get a handle on it.</p>",
